        "subject": "LU-17711 osd-ldiskfs: do not delete dotdot during rename",
        "message": "LU-17711 osd-ldiskfs: do not delete dotdot during rename\n\nSince upstream kernel commit v5.12-rc4-32-g6c0912739699\next4_dir_entry_2 after rec_len will be wiped when deleting\nthe entry.\nThis creates a problem with rename, when we delete dotdot\nfirst and if it's a dx dir, kernel will wipe entire dx_root\nin the block after dotdot entry.\n\nWe can just update the dotdot entry without deleting.\n\nFor dx dirs, ext4_update_dotdot() takes care the dotdot\nand inserting dotdot is an update already, use it for\nlinear dirs as well.\n\nImprove ext4-hash-indexed-dir-dotdot-update.patch,\nuse ext4_read_dirblock to get the first block.\n\nCleanup ext4-data-in-dirent.patch, now writing short\nform of dotdot without dirdata is also handled by\next4_update_dotdot().\n\nChange-Id: I4694e58bc415de477c78e193eac0b3376f5422d6\nSigned-off-by: Li Dongyang <dongyangli@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
